<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,527,1134]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,605,631]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Diagnoses to the genus are to be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Holdich" box="[855,1146,605,631]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" refString="Holdich D. M. &amp; Jones D. M. (1973) The systematics and ecology of a new genus of sand beach isopod (Sphaeromatidae) from Kenya. Journal of Zoology, London, 171, 385 - 395." type="journal article" year="1973">
Holdich &amp; Jones (
<number box="[1076,1137,605,631]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" value="1973.0">1973</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Schotte" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" refString="Schotte, M. &amp; Kensley, B. (2005) New species and records of Flabellifera from the Indian Ocean (Crustacea: Peracarida: Isopoda). Journal of Natural History, 39 (16), 1211 - 1282." type="journal article" year="2005">
Schotte &amp; Kensley (
<number box="[159,224,644,670]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,527,1134]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,320,682,708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">Remarks.</emphasis>
Diagnoses of this genus were provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Holdich" box="[851,1143,682,708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" refString="Holdich D. M. &amp; Jones D. M. (1973) The systematics and ecology of a new genus of sand beach isopod (Sphaeromatidae) from Kenya. Journal of Zoology, London, 171, 385 - 395." type="journal article" year="1973">
Holdich &amp; Jones (
<number box="[1073,1134,682,708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" value="1973.0">1973</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and later by Holdich &amp; Harrison (
<number box="[272,336,721,747]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" value="1987.0">1987</number>
), and 
<bibRefCitation author="Schotte" box="[409,727,721,747]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" refString="Schotte, M. &amp; Kensley, B. (2005) New species and records of Flabellifera from the Indian Ocean (Crustacea: Peracarida: Isopoda). Journal of Natural History, 39 (16), 1211 - 1282." type="journal article" year="2005">
Schotte &amp; Kensley (
<number box="[652,717,721,747]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. In contrast to the generic diagnosis given by these authors and based on examination of several species, we found that the sutures of the coxal plate are not visible in some species (e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="Storey, 2002" authorityName="Storey" authorityYear="2002" box="[386,771,798,824]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sphaeromatidae" genus="Sphaeromopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sei">
<emphasis box="[386,608,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">Sphaeromopsis sei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Storey" box="[617,771,798,824]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" refString="Storey M. (2002) New species and a new record of sphaeromatid isopods (Crustacea) from the Andaman Sea, Thailand. Phuket Marine Biological Center Special Publication, 23 (1), 133 - 148." type="journal article" year="2002">
Storey, 
<number box="[708,771,798,824]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Loyola" authorityName="Loyola" box="[784,991,798,824]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sphaeromatidae" genus="Sphaeromopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mourei">
<emphasis box="[784,898,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">S. mourei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Loyola" box="[906,991,798,824]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" refString="Loyola e Silva, J. de. (1960) Sphaeromatidae do litoral Brasiliero (Isopoda: Crustacea). Boletim da Universidade do Parana, Zoologia, 4, 1 - 182." type="journal article" year="1960">Loyola</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
e Silva, 
<number box="[1098,1161,798,824]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" value="1960.0">1960</number>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[1225,1394,799,824]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sphaeromatidae" genus="Sphaeromopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persikolpos" status="sp. nov">
<emphasis box="[1225,1394,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">S. persikolpos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="1" pageNumber="34" rank="species">sp. nov</taxonomicNameLabel>
). We also found that pleonal sutures vary in morphology and number; thus for example, in 
<taxonomicName authority="Schotte &amp; Kensley, 2005" authorityName="Schotte &amp; Kensley" authorityYear="2005" class="Malacostraca" family="Sphaeromatidae" genus="Sphaeromopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcifera">
<emphasis box="[1300,1435,837,862]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">S. sulcifera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schotte" box="[151,459,876,902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" refString="Schotte, M. &amp; Kensley, B. (2005) New species and records of Flabellifera from the Indian Ocean (Crustacea: Peracarida: Isopoda). Journal of Natural History, 39 (16), 1211 - 1282." type="journal article" year="2005">
Schotte &amp; Kensley, 
<number box="[395,459,876,902]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the sutures are not clearly visible, whereas in 
<taxonomicName box="[1032,1202,876,901]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sphaeromatidae" genus="Sphaeromopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persikolpos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1032,1202,876,901]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">S. persikolpos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1211,1308,875,901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1211,1308,875,901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, there is a single suture on either side of the posterior margin of the pleon. Although the pereon and pleon of most species in the genus do not exhibit any dorsal ornamentation, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kensley &amp; Schotte, 1994" authorityName="Kensley &amp; Schotte" authorityYear="1994" box="[879,1289,953,979]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sphaeromatidae" genus="Sphaeromopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heardi">
<emphasis box="[879,984,953,978]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">S. heardi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kensley" box="[992,1289,953,979]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" refString="Kensley, B. &amp; Schotte, M. (1994) Marine isopods from the Lesser Antilles and Colombia (Crustacea: Pericarida). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 107 (3), 482 - 510." type="journal article" year="1994">
Kensley &amp; Schotte, 
<number box="[1230,1289,953,979]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has obvious sculpturing on the pleotelson, and 
<taxonomicName box="[560,726,992,1017]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sphaeromatidae" genus="Sphaeromopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persikolpos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[560,726,992,1017]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">S. persikolpos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[734,828,991,1017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[734,828,991,1017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has some foraminate scattered setae on the surface of these sclerites. Moreover, the pleotelson varies in shapes from broadly truncate in 
<taxonomicName authority="Holdich &amp; Jones, 1973" authorityName="Holdich &amp; Jones" authorityYear="1973" class="Malacostraca" family="Sphaeromatidae" genus="Sphaeromopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amathitis">
<emphasis box="[1162,1302,1031,1056]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">S. amathitis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Holdich" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" refString="Holdich D. M. &amp; Jones D. M. (1973) The systematics and ecology of a new genus of sand beach isopod (Sphaeromatidae) from Kenya. Journal of Zoology, London, 171, 385 - 395." type="journal article" year="1973">
Holdich &amp; Jones, 
<number box="[232,291,1069,1095]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" value="1973.0">1973</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
to broadly rounded in 
<taxonomicName authority="Javed &amp; Yousuf, 1995" authorityName="Javed &amp; Yousuf" authorityYear="1995" box="[564,964,1069,1095]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sphaeromatidae" genus="Sphaeromopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis box="[564,689,1069,1094]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">S. minutus</emphasis>
Javed &amp; Yousuf, 
<number box="[902,964,1069,1095]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</taxonomicName>
, to elongated with a narrow apex in the Persian Gulf's species 
<taxonomicName box="[414,578,1108,1133]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sphaeromatidae" genus="Sphaeromopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persikolpos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[414,578,1108,1133]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">S. persikolpos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[586,679,1107,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[586,679,1107,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
